    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <div class="header-label">Eugene Schwartz Framework</div>
            <h1>Market Sophistication</h1>
            <p class="subtitle">"How many similar products have prospects been told about before?"</p>
        </header>

        <div class="intro-section">
            <h2>Understanding Market Sophistication</h2>
            <p>Market Sophistication is the third critical variable every copywriter must analyze before writing a headline. Eugene Schwartz teaches us that no market stands still‚Äîit evolves through predictable stages as prospects are exposed to more and more similar claims.</p>
            <blockquote>
                "How many similar products have [prospects] been told about before?"<br>
                <strong>‚Äî Eugene Schwartz</strong>
            </blockquote>
        </div>

        <div class="workflow-bar">
            <div class="workflow-step">
                <div class="workflow-step-num">STEP 1</div>
                <div class="workflow-step-name">Analyze Market</div>
            </div>
            <div class="workflow-step">
                <div class="workflow-step-num">STEP 2</div>
                <div class="workflow-step-name">Identify Stage</div>
            </div>
            <div class="workflow-step">
                <div class="workflow-step-num">STEP 3</div>
                <div class="workflow-step-name">Choose Strategy</div>
            </div>
            <div class="workflow-step">
                <div class="workflow-step-num">STEP 4</div>
                <div class="workflow-step-name">Write Headline</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- STAGE 1 -->
        <div class="stage-section">
            <div class="stage-header">
                <div class="stage-badge">
                    <div class="stage-badge-label">Stage</div>
                    <div class="stage-badge-num">01</div>
                </div>
                <div class="stage-content">
                    <h2>First in Your Market</h2>
                    <p class="stage-subtitle">The Dream Scenario: Virgin Territory</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="info-grid">
                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="info-card-header">
                        <div class="info-card-icon">üéØ</div>
                        <h3 class="info-card-title">The Strategy</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="info-card-content">
                        <strong>Be simple and direct. Do not be "fancy".</strong>
                        <p style="margin-top: 12px;">The prospect has no prior information about similar products. A raw promise is enough to capture their attention because the market is completely unsophisticated.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="info-card-header">
                        <div class="info-card-icon">üìù</div>
                        <h3 class="info-card-title">When to Use</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="info-card-content">
                        <ul>
                            <li>You're launching a truly new product category</li>
                            <li>Your audience has never heard of this solution</li>
                            <li>No competitors have made similar claims</li>
                            <li>The market is "virgin" and unsophisticated</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="info-card">
                    <div class="info-card-header">
                        <div class="info-card-icon">‚ö°</div>
                        <h3 class="info-card-title">How to Execute</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="info-card-content">
                        <ul>
                            <li>State the need or claim directly</li>
                            <li>Use simple, clear language</li>
                            <li>Don't overcomplicate the message</li>
                            <li>Focus on the core benefit only</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="example-box">
                <div class="example-label">Classic Example Headline</div>
                <div class="example-text">"NOW! LOSE UGLY FAT!"</div>
                <div class="example-explanation">Simple, direct, and powerful because the market had never heard this promise before.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="worksheet">
                <div class="worksheet-header">
                    <div class="worksheet-icon">‚úçÔ∏è</div>
